properties.areaDesc: Coastal waters from  Suwannee River to Keaton Beach out 20 NM; Apalachee Bay or Coastal Waters From Keaton Beach to Ochlockonee River Fl out to 20 Nm
properties.headline: Gale Watch issued February 5 at 2:44AM EST until February 7 at 1:00AM EST by NWS Tallahassee FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest winds 20 to 25 kt with gusts up to 40 kt and
seas 5 to 7 feet possible.

* WHERE...Nearshore Gulf waters from the Ochlockonee River to
the Suwannee River out 20 nautical miles.

* WHEN...From Thursday morning through late Thursday night.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should consider altering plans to avoid possible
hazardous conditions.  Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter
course, and/or secure the vessel for severe wind and seas.

NWSheadline: GALE WATCH IN EFFECT FROM THURSDAY MORNING THROUGH LATE THURSDAY NIGHT
